{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CH8absfzgWtC5PRBJiweBQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in place. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem root causes:**\n1. No MinIO Kubernetes Service existed — ES couldn't resolve `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n2. The `es-backups` bucket was never created (the `minio-init` Job failed because the service didn't exist yet)\n3. The `es-data-new-{0,1}` pods were missing S3 keystore entries entirely\n\n**Steps taken:**\n\n1. **Created MinIO Service** — `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` now resolves correctly\n\n2. **Created `es-secure-settings` Secret** — stores `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (both `minioadmin`); credentials stay out of `elasticsearch.yml` and env vars\n\n3. **Populated the keystore** on all 5 nodes (`es-cluster-{0,1,2}` and `es-data-new-{0,1}`) via `elasticsearch-keystore add --stdin --force` fed from the secret values\n\n4. **Reloaded secure settings** via `POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings` — no pod restarts needed\n\n5. **Created the `es-backups` bucket** in MinIO via `mc mb`\n\n6. **Registered `minio-repo`** snapshot repository (type `s3`, path-style access, HTTP protocol)\n\n7. **`snapshot-2` completed with `state: SUCCESS`** — 2 indices (`app-data`, `test-index`), 2/2 shards successful, 0 failures"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":821,"cache_read_input_tokens":53067,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":821},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2a6f3a1-ef91-480a-b3ef-335f53bcc58a","uuid":"21f63cc3-3db2-4f92-ad9f-54848bd61d6c","request_id":"req_011CcMfte6owWFX6dHDjcWfm"}
